        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Codex archived usage undercount",
        "body": "Fixes #1767\n\n## Summary\n- Keep Codex cache-read tokens as separate billable input instead of clamping them to non-cached input.\n- Only let a same-session Codex file suppress later files after it contributes usage in the scanned date range, so an active same-session stub does not hide archived billed rows.\n- Regenerate the Codex parser cache key and update pricing/priority tests for the separate input and cache-read semantics.\n\n## Tests\n- `Scripts/lint.sh lint`\n- `Scripts/regenerate-codex-parser-hash.sh --check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Core-only SwiftPM harness against the repository sources:\n  - `CostUsagePricingTests` (31 tests)\n  - `CostUsageScannerBreakdownTests` (43 tests)\n  - `CostUsageScannerPriorityTests` (14 tests)\n\nFull-package `swift test --filter CostUsagePricingTests --skip-update --disable-prefetching` did not complete locally because SwiftPM stalled while resolving the Sparkle 2.9.3 binary artifact.\n",
